<i>And lost my mind</i>

22
00:01:46.573 --> 00:01:50.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
THIS COUNTRY IS GOING TO GET
A LITTLE UNSETTLED

23
00:01:52.278 --> 00:01:54.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[crowd]
You're holding a board meeting?!

24
00:01:54.414 --> 00:01:55.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't that reckless?!

25
00:01:55.615 --> 00:01:57.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What will you do
if something happens?!

26
00:01:57.717 --> 00:02:01.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter what happens to me,
we will not give in to terrorists.

27
00:02:02.188 --> 00:02:03.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Chief Cabinet Secretary Mitsui.

28
00:02:04.157 --> 00:02:06.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In response
to these repeated acts of terrorism,

29
00:02:06.359 --> 00:02:09.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the government has made plans
at this meeting

30
00:02:09.462 --> 00:02:12.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to take special measures
against certain Ajin.

31
00:02:12.832 --> 00:02:14.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And along with these measures,</i>

32
00:02:14.901 --> 00:02:17.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>the ministries have come together</i>
<i>to form a new defense unit.</i>

33
00:02:18.338 --> 00:02:22.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The new unit will be called</i>
<i>the Anti-Ajin Special Forces.</i>

34
00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:27.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell...?

35
00:02:28.414 --> 00:02:32.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Forget about our civil rights, this just
keeps getting worse and worse! Damn it!

36
00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Anti-Ajin Special Forces?

37
00:02:36.656 --> 00:02:39.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How can we take on something like that?

38
00:02:39.359 --> 00:02:41.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tanaka, what are we going
to do about this?

39
00:02:41.394 --> 00:02:43.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we screw up,
we'll all end up in a lab!

40
00:02:45.498 --> 00:02:46.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I told you before...

41
00:02:47.667 --> 00:02:50.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
there's no turning back now.

42
00:02:50.403 --> 00:02:55.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yeah, but--
-There's nowhere to go back to now.

43
00:02:56.509 --> 00:03:00.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We just have to trust Sato.

44
00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:15.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is our new
and improved blinding laser.

45
00:03:15.862 --> 00:03:16.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please have a look.

46
00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:20.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Zero point three seconds
of exposure damages the retina,

47
00:03:20.266 --> 00:03:21.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
resulting in blindness.

48
00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:29.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've also increased the power
of this Taser gun to 2 million volts.

49
00:03:30.209 --> 00:03:33.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doesn't matter if you're an Ajin or not,
you will be immobilized instantly.

50
00:03:34.747 --> 00:03:36.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] It's wireless?

51
00:03:37.383 --> 00:03:43.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes. It's handy in a skirmish
and can now fire several shots in a row.

52
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:48.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've also made the impulse water cannons
smaller for dealing with IBMs.

53
00:03:49.495 --> 00:03:53.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, and we've prepared
smoke grenades as well.

54
00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:55.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And, finally, this...

55
00:03:56.769 --> 00:04:02.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An airburst grenade launcher, jointly
developed with a German arms maker.

56
00:04:02.909 --> 00:04:05.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It hasn't been deployed
in a real fight yet,

57
00:04:05.345 --> 00:04:08.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but when we tested it here,
they started calling it "The Executioner."

58
00:04:08.915 --> 00:04:10.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It made the folks here very happy.

59
00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:12.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Executioner, you say.

60
00:04:14.287 --> 00:04:18.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Since the grenade detonates
precisely above the target's head,

61
00:04:18.992 --> 00:04:21.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it renders
any sort of shielding ineffective.

62
00:04:22.895 --> 00:04:23.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have a look.

63
00:04:24.764 --> 00:04:28.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've verified how effective it is
by using it against the Ajin Tanaka.

64
00:04:30.803 --> 00:04:34.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The laser rangefinder measures
the distance to the target

65
00:04:34.607 --> 00:04:39.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and automatically sets the airburst
detonation position on the round's fuse.

66
00:04:42.415 --> 00:04:43.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
An outstanding weapon.

67
00:04:44.717 --> 00:04:46.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm pleased that you like it.

68
00:04:47.553 --> 00:04:49.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll prep one
for each member of your team.

69
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:53.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I honestly didn't think
they'd have progressed this far.

70
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:57.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In a few days,
Sato will be headed for the lab.

71
00:05:17.684 --> 00:05:19.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, that's right. Mr. Nekozawa.

72
00:05:20.787 --> 00:05:24.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Beginning next week some time,
you should probably go abroad for a while.

73
00:05:26.693 --> 00:05:29.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This country is going to get
a little unsettled.

74
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:34.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Sato, just how far
do you intend to take this?

75
00:05:35.068 --> 00:05:36.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

76
00:05:37.770 --> 00:05:39.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Until I've taken over the country.

77
00:05:46.579 --> 00:05:48.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nagai] <i>We're putting our plan</i>
<i>into motion in two days.</i>

78
00:05:48.881 --> 00:05:51.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This really will be our last chance.

79
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:54.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The field is going
to be Musashi Heavy Industries HQ.

80
00:05:55.822 --> 00:05:57.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
According to Mr. Tosaki's report,

81
00:05:57.790 --> 00:06:01.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the board meeting is going to be held
in the chairman's office on the top floor.

82
00:06:03.596 --> 00:06:07.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The AASF will be setting up a barricade
in the vicinity of the 24th floor.

83
00:06:08.401 --> 00:06:10.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're going to hide ourselves here.

84
00:06:11.037 --> 00:06:13.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The supply room
on the 21st floor would be ideal.

85
00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:16.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, when Sato and them attack,
we burst out and fight, yeah?

86
00:06:16.943 --> 00:06:19.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nagai] I haven't said anything
remotely like that.

87
00:06:20.913 --> 00:06:22.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] We just wait to start.

88
00:06:22.381 --> 00:06:25.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't want to get tangled up
in the fight between the AASF and Sato.

89
00:06:26.018 --> 00:06:26.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, right.

90
00:06:27.019 --> 00:06:29.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Sato takes out the AASF,
then we move.

91
00:06:30.156 --> 00:06:32.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Shimomura and myself
will handle close-quarters battles,

92
00:06:33.025 --> 00:06:34.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and you'll move to back us up, Nakano.

93
00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:38.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Tosaki, I'd like you
to be on radio support.

94
00:06:38.397 --> 00:06:40.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've already got my tools ready to go.

95
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:42.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That...

96
00:06:43.469 --> 00:06:45.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
leaves only one more problem.

97
00:06:46.472 --> 00:06:50.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As far as the measures we need to take
in order to intervene in the fight...

98
00:06:53.412 --> 00:06:55.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This isn't the same situation
as we had with the minister.

99
00:06:56.182 --> 00:06:59.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We should consider a different approach.
-Nobody asked you.

100
00:07:01.487 --> 00:07:04.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Come on, Mr. Tosaki,
don't tell me you're still mad.

101
00:07:04.457 --> 00:07:05.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut it.

102
00:07:06.626 --> 00:07:09.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll come up with something,
just like we planned.

103
00:07:19.639 --> 00:07:24.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki, I just can't agree with this.

104
00:07:25.211 --> 00:07:28.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This could land you in prison for life.
-Just shut up and drive.

105
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:32.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

106
00:07:55.875 --> 00:07:59.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Former foreign mercenary rejects
from the Self Defense Force?

107
00:07:59.846 --> 00:08:02.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They worked under my predecessor,
and I kept them on board.

108
00:08:03.182 --> 00:08:05.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With the minister's permission,
of course.

109
00:08:09.188 --> 00:08:12.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You want to use them as insurance
in case the AASF goes down?

110
00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:14.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exactly.

111
00:08:14.961 --> 00:08:17.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're used to handling Ajin

112
00:08:17.730 --> 00:08:19.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and professionals
when it comes to combat.

113
00:08:19.866 --> 00:08:21.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is out of the question.

114
00:08:23.936 --> 00:08:28.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Besides, you're off the commission.

115
00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:34.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only reason there's been no formal
dismissal is the minister's assassination.

116
00:08:34.847 --> 00:08:36.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's why I want one last chance.

117
00:08:36.649 --> 00:08:37.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cell phone ringing]

118
00:08:39.719 --> 00:08:40.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

119
00:08:42.622 --> 00:08:43.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, understood.

120
00:08:45.124 --> 00:08:46.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right there.

121
00:08:48.761 --> 00:08:51.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As you can see, I'm a busy man.

122
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:54.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forgive me, but I have to be going.

123
00:08:57.637 --> 00:08:59.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That day that we were attacked here,

124
00:09:00.806 --> 00:09:02.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I killed the Defense Department agent.

125
00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:07.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They found out
about us keeping Dr. Ogura.

126
00:09:09.615 --> 00:09:10.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it all.

127
00:09:12.285 --> 00:09:14.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell are you saying?

128
00:09:15.988 --> 00:09:17.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you finally lost your mind?

129
00:09:19.058 --> 00:09:20.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps.

130
00:09:21.294 --> 00:09:24.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if I let this get out,

131
00:09:25.798 --> 00:09:28.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you and I are both going to hell.

132
00:09:29.835 --> 00:09:30.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why me?

133
00:09:32.805 --> 00:09:34.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] <i>Ikuya Ogura is alive.</i>

134
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:38.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I've gotta hand it to him.</i>

135
00:09:39.278 --> 00:09:41.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To think he'd meddle
with one of the Americans...

136
00:09:48.654 --> 00:09:50.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We know nothing about this.
Is that clear?

137
00:09:51.757 --> 00:09:53.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We know nothing.

138
00:09:56.062 --> 00:09:58.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Mr. Tosaki is acting entirely</i>
<i>under his own authority.</i>

139
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:07.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Classic organized crime.

140
00:10:09.642 --> 00:10:11.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Guess I'll be seeing you in hell, friend.

141
00:10:18.184 --> 00:10:21.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, we're adding four people
to the security force?

142
00:10:21.721 --> 00:10:22.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Five.

143
00:10:23.089 --> 00:10:24.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll have Shimomura with me.

144
00:10:29.261 --> 00:10:30.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, and one more thing.

145
00:10:31.931 --> 00:10:32.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's something else?

146
00:10:33.032 --> 00:10:35.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] Put me back on the commission.

147
00:10:36.335 --> 00:10:37.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] <i>Yes. This is Security.</i>

148
00:10:39.205 --> 00:10:40.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

149
00:10:40.706 --> 00:10:41.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Mr. Sokabe?</i>

150
00:10:49.081 --> 00:10:50.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, things went well?

151
00:10:58.090 --> 00:10:59.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I got this for you.

152
00:11:08.367 --> 00:11:09.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki...

153
00:11:13.205 --> 00:11:14.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry about the oth--

154
00:11:18.377 --> 00:11:20.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were simply doing your job.

155
00:11:21.781 --> 00:11:23.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nothing to apologize for.

156
00:11:25.985 --> 00:11:27.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing? Let's go.

157
00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:31.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

158
00:11:40.466 --> 00:11:43.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our secret weapon's ready just in time.

159
00:11:47.907 --> 00:11:49.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] It's beautiful.

160
00:11:54.013 --> 00:11:58.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TOUTO UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

161
00:12:11.931 --> 00:12:15.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MUSASHI HEAVY INDUSTRIES

162
00:12:19.839 --> 00:12:20.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, that's the...

163
00:12:22.108 --> 00:12:23.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, the AASF.

164
00:12:26.078 --> 00:12:31.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm coming to you 500 meters
from the HQ of Musashi Heavy Industries.

165
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:35.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is now less than six hours until
the time Sato has said he will attack.

166
00:12:35.955 --> 00:12:39.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Sources have told us that Anti-Ajin</i>
<i>Special Forces have been deployed</i>

167
00:12:39.525 --> 00:12:41.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and are on guard.</i>

168
00:12:42.128 --> 00:12:45.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Musashi Heavy Industries has also ordered</i>
<i>an evacuation of all its employees.</i>

169
00:12:45.831 --> 00:12:50.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Only Chairman Hashiguchi and several of</i>
<i>the board members remain in the office.</i>

170
00:12:56.475 --> 00:12:58.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tonight,

171
00:12:58.777 --> 00:13:01.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we're going to bring the hammer down
on the last corporation

172
00:13:02.014 --> 00:13:06.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that treats Ajin like economic animals,</i>
<i>subjecting us to monstrous experiments.</i>

173
00:13:08.320 --> 00:13:15.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This will be a giant step towards
the future that we are aiming for.

174
00:13:17.796 --> 00:13:21.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We leave at 1700 hours.

175
00:13:22.001 --> 00:13:23.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's make some noise.

176
00:13:50.229 --> 00:13:51.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry for the wait!

177
00:13:52.898 --> 00:13:55.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both panting]

178
00:14:00.406 --> 00:14:01.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Izumi] <i>We're in position.</i>

179
00:14:02.041 --> 00:14:03.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Roger that.

180
00:14:03.209 --> 00:14:06.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
FK, do you copy? We're counting on you
for ghost countermeasures.

181
00:14:08.013 --> 00:14:10.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's no way to address a genius.

182
00:14:10.249 --> 00:14:12.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki] <i>Give orders the instant</i>
<i>there are any indications.</i>

183
00:14:14.119 --> 00:14:18.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter how you slice it, I can't
really imagine we'll need the insurance.

184
00:14:18.591 --> 00:14:21.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Agreed. If the AASF can't beat him,

185
00:14:21.427 --> 00:14:24.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there'll be no one left in this country
who can stop Sato.

186
00:14:24.463 --> 00:14:25.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] This is Comm 1,
satellite settings complete.

187
00:14:25.998 --> 00:14:29.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've even got satellites?
Sparing no expense, I see.

188
00:14:29.134 --> 00:14:31.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We got permission
from the cabinet secretary.

189
00:14:31.570 --> 00:14:33.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The government isn't messing around.

190
00:14:33.439 --> 00:14:35.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're going to put an end
to this nonsense today.

191
00:14:49.021 --> 00:14:50.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] <i>Under five minutes to go.</i>

192
00:14:50.522 --> 00:14:52.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>No change on the satellite image.</i>

193
00:15:00.666 --> 00:15:03.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 1] <i>Point Two. All clear.</i>
-[man 2] <i>This is Point Three. All clear.</i>

194
00:15:03.535 --> 00:15:05.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 3] <i>Point Four here. All clear.</i>

195
00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:06.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's their plan?

196
00:15:06.605 --> 00:15:09.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, they won't be able
to take down the building.

197
00:15:09.074 --> 00:15:11.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no way
they can pull that off this time.

198
00:15:12.177 --> 00:15:14.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our anti-airline terror measures
are in place.

199
00:15:14.647 --> 00:15:16.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've also closed off the sewers.

200
00:15:17.016 --> 00:15:20.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is an impregnable fortress.</i>

201
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:26.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] <i>Well, let's get this started,</i>
<i>shall we?</i>

202
00:15:26.425 --> 00:15:27.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Roger.

203
00:15:32.231 --> 00:15:33.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Chairman, it's almost time.

204
00:15:34.066 --> 00:15:36.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm? Ah.

205
00:15:43.609 --> 00:15:44.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's get started.

206
00:15:46.512 --> 00:15:48.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NO ENTRY

207
00:15:55.454 --> 00:15:57.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hey! Stop right there!
-Unauthorized vehicle!

208
00:16:03.729 --> 00:16:07.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] <i>This is Point Two! An unauthorized</i>
<i>vehicle has stopped at the barricade!</i>

209
00:16:07.132 --> 00:16:08.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're coming from the front?!

210
00:16:08.634 --> 00:16:10.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like moths to the flame.

211
00:16:11.003 --> 00:16:13.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry about casualties!
Just secure it!

212
00:16:13.405 --> 00:16:17.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To anyone onboard! Get out of the vehicle
with both hands in the air! Now!

213
00:16:18.377 --> 00:16:19.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get out!

214
00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:24.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got him!

215
00:16:25.551 --> 00:16:26.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All too easy.

216
00:16:26.518 --> 00:16:28.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Secure the vehicle!

217
00:16:36.462 --> 00:16:38.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

218
00:16:44.269 --> 00:16:47.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why, it's our secret weapon of course.

219
00:17:05.591 --> 00:17:08.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We need power! Power!

220
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:09.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?!

221
00:17:11.096 --> 00:17:12.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's coming down!

222
00:17:13.699 --> 00:17:15.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Run for cover!

223
00:17:36.622 --> 00:17:38.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're up, Okuyama.

224
00:17:46.832 --> 00:17:49.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How...? How could this...?

225
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:52.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What happened?!
-Report!

226
00:17:52.538 --> 00:17:55.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All electronics are down!
They won't reboot!

227
00:17:55.707 --> 00:17:57.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've lost all power!

228
00:17:58.544 --> 00:18:02.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Shimomura, do you copy?
Shimomura?! Damn it.

229
00:18:02.448 --> 00:18:03.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?

230
00:18:06.785 --> 00:18:08.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
An EMP.

231
00:18:09.455 --> 00:18:13.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They made an explosive generator.

232
00:18:13.692 --> 00:18:16.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And that energy fries the circuitry
in any electronic device.

233
00:18:17.696 --> 00:18:22.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every piece of electronics within a radius
of several hundred meters is likely dead.

234
00:18:23.135 --> 00:18:23.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

235
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[drones whirring]

236
00:18:28.407 --> 00:18:29.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell?

237
00:18:31.710 --> 00:18:32.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Open fire!

238
00:18:34.580 --> 00:18:35.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's make some noise.

239
00:18:44.857 --> 00:18:46.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it...

240
00:18:48.794 --> 00:18:53.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love it when a plan comes together.

241
00:19:02.641 --> 00:19:04.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, the anchor has been placed.

242
00:19:05.244 --> 00:19:06.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pull the lead rope.

243
00:19:06.512 --> 00:19:07.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Roger.

244
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:10.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?

245
00:19:11.383 --> 00:19:12.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yo, Nagai!

246
00:19:12.484 --> 00:19:13.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take it easy, Nakano.

247
00:19:14.353 --> 00:19:15.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let your eyes adjust first.

248
00:19:16.755 --> 00:19:18.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki. Mr. Tosaki!

249
00:19:19.458 --> 00:19:21.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No good. The radios are dead, too.

250
00:19:21.727 --> 00:19:23.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What should--? What should we do?!

251
00:19:23.595 --> 00:19:25.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just settle down, Nakano.

252
00:19:25.497 --> 00:19:27.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We just need to wait like planned.
-No.

253
00:19:30.235 --> 00:19:31.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's move.

254
00:19:37.809 --> 00:19:39.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] <i>Now I'm an electrician?</i>

255
00:19:40.479 --> 00:19:42.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More like a power line technician.

256
00:19:43.916 --> 00:19:49.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Airburst grenade launcher, Taser gun,
blinding laser, all unusable.

257
00:19:50.189 --> 00:19:51.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our comm equipment is down, too.

258
00:19:52.591 --> 00:19:54.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This situation may actually
have given us a chance.

259
00:19:55.961 --> 00:19:57.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have an idea.

260
00:19:58.797 --> 00:20:02.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Discard all your electronics.
We're going with standard equipment.

261
00:20:02.401 --> 00:20:04.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[glass breaking then guns cocking]

262
00:20:10.475 --> 00:20:15.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] And now, a primal fight,
with only fire and blades.

263
00:20:18.483 --> 00:20:20.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exciting, isn't it?

264
00:20:24.256 --> 00:20:25.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is this actually gonna work?

265
00:20:25.958 --> 00:20:28.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato's a man of his word.

266
00:20:28.994 --> 00:20:30.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that's going to be his undoing.

267
00:20:32.364 --> 00:20:34.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's put our plan into action.

268
00:20:44.610 --> 00:20:46.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TO BE CONTINUED

269
00:20:47.813 --> 00:20:50.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chorus singing]
<i>I'm tired of this one already, so</i>

270
00:20:50.916 --> 00:20:54.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'll trade it</i>

271
00:20:54.386 --> 00:20:59.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For your ordinary one</i>

272
00:21:00.659 --> 00:21:06.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A shiny holy card</i>

273
00:21:06.965 --> 00:21:12.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For a grainy paper card</i>

274
00:21:13.438 --> 00:21:17.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can see them all</i>

275
00:21:19.778 --> 00:21:24.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When you come to my house</i>

276
00:21:24.383 --> 00:21:30.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So</i>
